                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre. The 6th order vowel marker of ጵ is
                           attached to the upper vertical stroke at the right side (<locus target="#13rb">13rb</locus>).</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12820TawMad">Tawalda Madḫǝn</persName>, the scribe, is mentioned in the supplication formulas on <locus target="#3va">3va</locus>, 41vb, 45ra, 51rb and in the concluding
                        supplication formula on <locus target="#60rb">60rb</locus>.<date notBefore="1950" notAfter="2000">Second half
                           of the 20th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡ ዓ, ለ፡ ዓ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#39rb">39rb</locus>, 45rb, 47va, 48va, 50rb, 51rb, 55vb,
                              58ra)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>አ፡</abbr> for <expan>አሜን፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#55rb">55rb</locus>, 58ra)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the protagonist; second
                           components of the names of the donor, her family members and the scribe;
                           groups of lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page of
                           Texts I and II; incipits of sections/miracles; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic"><seg type="script">Very poor hand of additio 1</seg><date notBefore="1950" notAfter="2000">Second half
                        of the 20th century</date></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#60va">f. 60va</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText"> Unidentified prayer to Mary of Zion.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           
                           <note> The note is written by a very poor hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- The word za-Mikāʾel “of Michael” is written in the outer
                           margin of <locus target="#18r">18r</locus>. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>- A directive for the
                           ministers is written in the upper margin of <locus target="#39ra">39ra</locus>, by the main hand: ወኮነ፡ ዕረፍቱ፡ አመ፡ ፭ለመጋቢት፡ ዘይትነብብ፡ በዝ፡
                           ወርኅ “And he passed away on 5th Maggābit, it is read in that month”</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc>
                           Pen trials: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 60v.
 - Writing
                           exercises, doodles: e.g., fols. 1r, 18r, 60v.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Monthly readings of Text I are indicated by the
                              names of the months crudely written in pencil by secondary hands, in
                              the upper margin of some fols.: Maggābit: <locus target="#3ra">fol.
                                 3ra</locus> za-Miyāzyā: fols. 6vb, 7vb za-Gǝnbot: <locus target="#9vb">fol. 9vb</locus> Ḥamle: <locus target="#13rb">fol.
                                    13rb</locus> Naḥāse: <locus target="#17ra">fol. 17ra</locus>.
                              za-Maskaram: <locus target="#30vb">fol. 30vb</locus> za-Ḫǝdār: <locus target="#34va">fol. 34va</locus> za-Ṭǝqǝmt: <locus target="#34vb">fol. 34vb</locus> Ṭǝrr: <locus target="#41vb">fol.
                              41vb</locus>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards (both broken and repaired).
 Two
                           pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Two rows of small holes are visible on
                           the spinefolds of the quires.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">None</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
